[i]Explore, inspect, and understand your Garry’s Mod addons in real time.[/i]

[h2]How to use[/h2]

Open the gPeek interface in-game from the spawnmenu and browse your installed addons. Click files to instantly preview them using the appropriate viewer.

Addon nodes all offer different options on right click, from copying file paths to copying file contents. Some viewers also implement right click features directly. For example, selecting text in the code viewer and right clicking will copy the selection to the clipboard.

[h2]Preferences[/h2]

You can change the code viewer theme, font and font size in [b]Utilities > User > Code Viewer Settings[/b] from the extended spawnmenu.

[table]
[tr]
[th]ConVar[/th]
[th]Description[/th]
[/tr]
[tr]
[td]gpeek_batch_size[/td]
[td]Number of files to process per batch. Default: 10. Min: 1. Max: 100.[/td]
[/tr]
[tr]
[td]gpeek_batch_delay[/td]
[td]Processing delay between each file batch. Default: 0.00. Min: 0.00. Max: 1.00.[/td]
[/tr]
[tr]
[td]gpeek_multi_addon[/td]
[td]Allow expanding multiple addons. Default: 0. To allow: 1.[/td]
[/tr]
[/table]

The theme seen above can be found here: 
[url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2977952965]Derma Github Dark Theme Skin[/url]

[h2]Key Features[/h2]

[b]🔎 Browse all your addon files in-game[/b]
Navigate your installed addons through a fast, expandable file tree.

[b]📄 Code viewing[/b]
Read Lua and other text-based files with syntax highlighting, line numbers, and original formatting.

[b]🖼️ Preview almost anything[/b]
Includes built-in viewers for:
[list]
[*] Models (with animations, skins, bodygroups)
  [list]
    [*] You can also rotate and move the model with left click / right click. Mouse wheel to zoom.
  [/list]
[*] Images and materials
[*] Audio with live visualization
[*] Fonts
[*] Particles (Requires Particle Effects+)
[*] Code and text files
[/list]

[b]⚡ Fast, optimized, interactive[/b]
Designed to avoid frame drops using background loading and smart batching.

[h2]What is this for?[/h2]
[list]
[*] Exploring how addons are built
[*] Debugging and inspecting game content
[*] Previewing models, materials, and audio without leaving the game
[*] Learning from existing GLua code
[/list]
It is designed as both a developer tool and a general-purpose addon browser.

[h2]Requirements[/h2]

The following are soft requirements, the addon will still work without them:
[list]
[*] [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3684885115]Particle Effects+[/url]
[/list]

[h2]Notes[/h2]
[list]
[*] This project is experimental and built for fun / personal use
[*] Performance may vary depending on number of installed addons
[*] Some file types depend on optional systems or other addons
[/list]

